      • decode

        public String decode(byte[] imageData,
                     int imageWidth,
                     int imageHeight)
              throws DeviceException
        Initialize the decode engine, pay attention to the use of exit(). Note: Image data cannot exceed the limited size of the binder transaction buffer(currently 1Mb), otherwise, the call will fail and TransactionTooLargeException will be thrown.
        Parameters:
        imageData - Image data, here image data must be grayscale image data, and must be a byte representing a pixel
        imageWidth - Image width
        imageHeight - Image height
        Returns:
        Decoding failed: returns null; decoding succeeds: returns the corresponding string
        Throws:
        DeviceException

      • exit

        DeviceException

                              int value)
                       throws DeviceException
        Set the decode library properties, such as setting a code system on or off
        Parameters:
        propertyClass - Property class, currently only supports CLASS_CODE, can be set to CLASS_CODE
        key - key, see DecodePropertyKey
        value - Set the value of this key，see DecodePropertyValue
        Throws:
        DeviceException
